md:
giải nghĩa từ "overtime" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan và các từ trái nghĩa.

**Overtime** (noun)

* Meaning: additional time worked beyond the normal working hours, usually to complete a task or project.
* Vietnamese translation: giờ làm thêm, giờ vượt quá giờ làm việc bình thường.

Example sentence: "I had to work overtime to finish the project on time."

* Related words: extra time, extended hours, additional work.
* Antonyms: regular hours, standard working hours.

**Overtime** (verb)

* Meaning: to work longer than the normal working hours.
* Vietnamese translation: làm thêm giờ, vượt quá giờ làm việc bình thường.

Example sentence: "I will have to overtime tonight to meet the deadline."

* Related words: work extra, put in extra hours, work longer.
* Antonyms: clock out, finish work, stop working.

Note: The verb form of "overtime" is less common than the noun form, but it is still used in some contexts.
